Looking at the repository, I need to implement rate limiting on the login endpoint to prevent credential stuffing attacks while ensuring the refresh token endpoint remains unaffected for mobile app compatibility.

Based on the requirements:
1. Rate limit by IP+username combination (not IP alone)
2. Allow 5 failed attempts per 10-minute window
3. Implement exponential backoff: 1-min (after 5 fails), 5-min (after 10), 15-min (after 15)
4. Reset counter on successful login
5. Include rate limit headers in response
6. Log failed attempts (without passwords)
7. Do NOT rate limit the refresh endpoint

